Detailed Description

FM Multi-way Partitioning Common Utility. This class is mainly reponsible for calculating the initial gain and calculating the amount of the gain change (delta gain) according to the move.

void FMKWayPartComm::initGainKMinus1 ( const Net &  e,
const std::vector< unsigned char > &  part 
) [protected]

Setup the initial gain with (K-1) metric. Also setup the gain buckets data structure. Take O(n) time.

Note that the code for (K-1) metric looks similar to the bi-partitioning code. Setting the initial gain for each net. Here, we use the (K-1) metric cost model.

References _num, PinForNetCursorTmpl< Net_, Pin_ >::count(), FMKWayPartMgrBase::getNumPartitions(), and Net::getWeight().

void FMKWayPartComm::initGainSOED ( const Net &  e,
const std::vector< unsigned char > &  part 
) [protected]

Setup the initial gain with SOED metric. Also setup the gain buckets data structure. Take O(n) time.

Note that SOED cost is equal to the (K-1) cost plus the Hyper Edge cost.

References _num, PinForNetCursorTmpl< Net_, Pin_ >::count(), FMKWayPartMgrBase::getNumPartitions(), and Net::getWeight().
